This is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on January 13, 2017. The memorandum provides an order of succession within the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service. According to the memorandum, in the event that the Director of the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service is unable to perform their duties, the Deputy Director of Field Operations, Deputy Director, and Manager of National Programs and Initiatives will act as and perform the functions of the Director in the specified order. The memorandum also includes exemptions and provisions, such as the President's discretion to depart from the memorandum in designating an acting Director.